I now have all the information needed to produce a comprehensive, precise implementation plan. Here it is:

---

## PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Detailed Implementation Plan

### Overview

PulseBoard is a multi-account channel plugin modeled after the IRC plugin. It uses `createScopedChannelConfigAdapter`, supports `"direct"` and `"group"` chat types, authenticates via `apiToken` + `serverUrl`, and probes via HTTP GET to `<serverUrl>/health`. Boards are `#`-prefixed group targets; DMs use plain usernames.

---

### 1. File Structure

All files live under `extensions/pulseboard/`:

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── package.json
├── openclaw.plugin.json
├── index.ts
├── setup-entry.ts
├── channel-config-api.ts
├── api.ts
└── src/
    ├── types.ts
    ├── accounts.ts
    ├── config-schema.ts
    ├── config-ui-hints.ts
    ├── normalize.ts
    ├── client.ts
    ├── probe.ts
    ├── send.ts
    ├── monitor.ts
    ├── inbound.ts
    ├── policy.ts
    ├── runtime-api.ts
    ├── runtime.ts
    ├── setup-core.ts
    ├── setup-surface.ts
    └── channel.ts
```

Test files (co-located in `src/`):
```
    ├── accounts.test.ts
    ├── config-schema.test.ts
    ├── normalize.test.ts
    ├── probe.test.ts
    ├── send.test.ts
    └── channel.test.ts
```

---

### 2. File-by-File Implementation Details

#### `extensions/pulseboard/package.json`

Mirrors `@openclaw/irc`'s structure with the PulseBoard-specific identity:

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw PulseBoard channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "devDependencies": {
    "openclaw": "workspace:*"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "openclaw": ">=2026.4.1-beta.1"
  },
  "peerDependenciesMeta": {
    "openclaw": { "optional": true }
  },
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "install": { "minHostVersion": ">=2026.4.1" },
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (Server + Token)",
      "detailLabel": "PulseBoard",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "docsLabel": "pulseboard",
      "blurb": "real-time bulletin board with #boards and DMs.",
      "aliases": ["pulse-board"],
      "systemImage": "network"
    }
  }
}
```

Key decisions: No external runtime dependencies since the HTTP client uses the built-in `fetch` API. This keeps the plugin lean.

---

#### `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

---

#### `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts`

Defines all TypeScript types for the plugin. Imports SDK types through `./runtime-api.js` (the private barrel) to stay within the boundary.

```typescript
import type {
  DmPolicy,
  GroupPolicy,
  MarkdownConfig,
  OpenClawConfig,
  BaseProbeResult,
} from "./runtime-api.js";

// Per-board config (analogous to IrcChannelConfig)
export type PulseBoardChannelConfig = {
  requireMention?: boolean;
  enabled?: boolean;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  systemPrompt?: string;
};

// Per-account config (analogous to IrcAccountConfig)
export type PulseBoardAccountConfig = {
  name?: string;
  enabled?: boolean;
  serverUrl?: string;
  apiToken?: string;
  apiTokenFile?: string;
  dmPolicy?: DmPolicy;
  allowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  defaultTo?: string;
  groupPolicy?: GroupPolicy;
  groupAllowFrom?: Array<string | number>;
  boards?: Record<string, PulseBoardChannelConfig>;
  markdown?: MarkdownConfig;
};

// Top-level config section (accounts + shared config)
export type PulseBoardConfig = PulseBoardAccountConfig & {
  accounts?: Record<string, PulseBoardAccountConfig>;
  defaultAccount?: string;
};

// CoreConfig augmentation (analogous to IrcConfig's CoreConfig)
export type CoreConfig = OpenClawConfig & {
  channels?: OpenClawConfig["channels"] & {
    pulseboard?: PulseBoardConfig;
  };
};

// Inbound message shape from the PulseBoard WebSocket/long-poll feed
export type PulseBoardInboundMessage = {
  messageId: string;
  /** Board name (e.g. "#general") for group messages, sender username for DMs */
  target: string;
  senderUsername: string;
  text: string;
  timestamp: number;
  isGroup: boolean;
};

// Probe result shape
export type PulseBoardProbe = BaseProbeResult<string> & {
  serverUrl: string;
  latencyMs?: number;
};
```

Key decisions:
- `boards` mirrors IRC's `groups`/`channels` concept. A board is a `#`-prefixed target.
- `apiTokenFile` parallels IRC's `passwordFile` for secret-file support.
- `PulseBoardInboundMessage` is intentionally simple since PulseBoard has no IRC-style `senderUser`/`senderHost` identity components.

---

#### `extensions/pulseboard/src/accounts.ts`

Resolves account configuration, reads env vars (`PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN` for default account only), and handles secret-file token loading.

Imports:
```typescript
import { createAccountListHelpers } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers";
import { DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID, normalizeAccountId } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id";
import { resolveMergedAccountConfig } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution";
import { normalizeResolvedSecretInputString, tryReadSecretFileSync } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input";
import type { CoreConfig, PulseBoardAccountConfig } from "./types.js";
```

Exported types and functions:

```typescript
export type ResolvedPulseBoardAccount = {
  accountId: string;
  enabled: boolean;
  name?: string;
  configured: boolean;          // true iff serverUrl AND apiToken are both non-empty
  serverUrl: string;
  apiToken: string;
  apiTokenSource: "env" | "tokenFile" | "config" | "none";
  config: PulseBoardAccountConfig;
};

export const {
  listAccountIds: listPulseBoardAccountIds,
  resolveDefaultAccountId: resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId,
} = createAccountListHelpers("pulseboard", { normalizeAccountId });

// Internal: merge base + per-account config using resolveMergedAccountConfig
function mergePulseBoardAccountConfig(cfg: CoreConfig, accountId: string): PulseBoardAccountConfig

// Internal: resolve apiToken from env (default account only), tokenFile, or config value
function resolveApiToken(accountId: string, merged: PulseBoardAccountConfig): {
  apiToken: string;
  source: "env" | "tokenFile" | "config" | "none";
}

export function resolvePulseBoardAccount(params: {
  cfg: CoreConfig;
  accountId?: string | null;
}): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount
```

Implementation details for `resolvePulseBoardAccount`:
1. Normalize `accountId` with `normalizeAccountId`.
2. Merge config using `resolveMergedAccountConfig` with `omitKeys: ["defaultAccount"]` and no `nestedObjectKeys` (PulseBoard has no nested credential objects).
3. For default account: try `process.env.PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN?.trim()` first, then `merged.apiTokenFile`, then `merged.apiToken` via `normalizeResolvedSecretInputString`.
4. `configured = Boolean(serverUrl.trim() && apiToken.trim())`.
5. Apply the same fallback-to-configured-account pattern as IRC: if the primary account is not configured and no explicit accountId was given, try `resolveDefaultPulseBoardAccountId` as a fallback.

```typescript
export function listEnabledPulseBoardAccounts(cfg: CoreConfig): ResolvedPulseBoardAccount[]
```

---

#### `extensions/pulseboard/src/config-schema.ts`

Defines Zod schemas for config validation.

Imports:
```typescript
import {
  buildChannelConfigSchema,
  DmPolicySchema,
  GroupPolicySchema,
  MarkdownConfigSchema,
  requireOpenAllowFrom,
  AllowFromListSchema,
} from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema";
import { z } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/zod";
import { pulseBoardChannelConfigUiHints } from "./config-ui-hints.js";
```

Schemas:

```typescript
const PulseBoardGroupSchema = z.object({
  requireMention: z.boolean().optional(),
  enabled: z.boolean().optional(),
  allowFrom: z.array(z.union([z.string(), z.number()])).optional(),
  systemPrompt: z.string().optional(),
}).strict();

export const PulseBoardAccountSchemaBase = z.object({
  name: z.string().optional(),
  enabled: z.boolean().optional(),
  serverUrl: z.string().optional(),
  apiToken: z.string().optional(),
  apiTokenFile: z.string().optional(),
  dmPolicy: DmPolicySchema.optional().default("pairing"),
  allowFrom: z.array(z.union([z.string(), z.number()])).optional(),
  groupPolicy: GroupPolicySchema.optional().default("allowlist"),
  groupAllowFrom: z.array(z.union([z.string(), z.number()])).optional(),
  boards: z.record(z.string(), PulseBoardGroupSchema.optional()).optional(),
  markdown: MarkdownConfigSchema,
  defaultTo: z.string().optional(),
}).strict();

export const PulseBoardAccountSchema = PulseBoardAccountSchemaBase.superRefine((value, ctx) => {
  requireOpenAllowFrom({
    policy: value.dmPolicy,
    allowFrom: value.allowFrom,
    ctx,
    path: ["allowFrom"],
    message: 'channels.pulseboard.dmPolicy="open" requires channels.pulseboard.allowFrom to include "*"',
  });
});

export const PulseBoardConfigSchema = PulseBoardAccountSchemaBase.extend({
  accounts: z.record(z.string(), PulseBoardAccountSchema.optional()).optional(),
  defaultAccount: z.string().optional(),
}).superRefine((value, ctx) => {
  requireOpenAllowFrom({
    policy: value.dmPolicy,
    allowFrom: value.allowFrom,
    ctx,
    path: ["allowFrom"],
    message: 'channels.pulseboard.dmPolicy="open" requires channels.pulseboard.allowFrom to include "*"',
  });
});

export const PulseBoardChannelConfigSchema = buildChannelConfigSchema(PulseBoardConfigSchema, {
  uiHints: pulseBoardChannelConfigUiHints,
});
```

Note: no `ReplyRuntimeConfigSchemaShape` is spread in since PulseBoard keeps its config simpler than IRC. This can be added later if block-streaming or chunk-mode tuning are needed.

---

#### `extensions/pulseboard/src/config-ui-hints.ts`

```typescript
import type { ChannelConfigUiHint } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/core";

export const pulseBoardChannelConfigUiHints = {
  "": {
    label: "PulseBoard",
    help: "PulseBoard channel provider configuration. Connect to a PulseBoard server for #board and direct messaging.",
  },
  serverUrl: {
    label: "PulseBoard Server URL",
    help: "Base URL of the PulseBoard server (e.g. https://pb.example.com).",
  },
  apiToken: {
    label: "PulseBoard API Token",
    help: "API token for authentication (sensitive). Use apiTokenFile for file-based secrets.",
  },
  apiTokenFile: {
    label: "PulseBoard API Token File",
    help: "Optional file path containing the PulseBoard API token.",
  },
  dmPolicy: {
    label: "PulseBoard DM Policy",
    help: 'Direct message access control ("pairing" recommended). "open" requires channels.pulseboard.allowFrom=["*"].',
  },
