# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

This plan adds a new fictional **PulseBoard** channel plugin to OpenClaw. PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board platform where users post to named boards (group chat) and can also send direct messages. The plugin must follow the same extension structure as existing bundled channel plugins (IRC, Nostr). No existing files may be modified — all work lives under `extensions/pulseboard/`.

---

## Design Decisions

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Plugin ID | `pulseboard` |
| Package name | `@openclaw/pulseboard` |
| Config path | `channels.pulseboard` |
| Chat types | `["direct", "group"]` |
| Text chunk limit | 4000 chars |
| Media support | false |
| Auth | `apiToken` + `serverUrl` |
| Env var | `PULSEBOARD_API_TOKEN` (default account only) |
| Account model | Multi-account (`createScopedChannelConfigAdapter`, mirroring IRC) |
| Board targets | `#board-name` prefix |
| DM targets | plain `username` or `@username` |
| Configured check | `Boolean(serverUrl && apiToken)` |
| Probe method | HTTP GET to `<serverUrl>/health` |

---

## File Structure

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── openclaw.plugin.json          # Plugin manifest
├── package.json                  # Package metadata with openclaw block
├── index.ts                      # Main entry point
├── setup-entry.ts                # Setup-only entry point
├── api.ts                        # Public API barrel
├── channel-config-api.ts         # Config schema export
└── src/
    ├── types.ts                  # TypeScript type definitions
    ├── config-schema.ts          # Zod validation schemas
    ├── accounts.ts               # Account listing and resolution
    ├── runtime.ts                # Runtime store
    ├── runtime-api.ts            # Aggregating SDK barrel
    ├── normalize.ts              # Target/entry normalization
    ├── send.ts                   # Outbound message delivery
    ├── probe.ts                  # Health check
    ├── monitor.ts                # Inbound message loop (simulated)
    ├── inbound.ts                # Inbound message processing
    ├── policy.ts                 # Group/board policy helpers
    ├── setup-core.ts             # Low-level config patching
    ├── setup-surface.ts          # Interactive setup wizard
    └── channel.ts                # ChannelPlugin implementation
```

Test files (co-located):
```
    src/normalize.test.ts
    src/config-schema.test.ts
    src/accounts.test.ts
    src/channel.test.ts
```

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1: `openclaw.plugin.json`

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

### Step 2: `package.json`

Mirror `extensions/irc/package.json`. Key fields:

```json
